# /cad-coder

cad-coder is a dispatcher skill. Keep this file small. Load the reference file
that matches the current turn, then act.

## Reference Loading

Always load:

- `cad-coder/references/core-workflow.md` for any CAD build, edit, validation,
  or export.

Load only when relevant:

- `cad-coder/references/zeroentropy-stl-references.md` before first-turn CAD
  for recognizable from-scratch objects such as toys, brackets, holders,
  household parts, mechanisms, or public/common objects.
- `cad-coder/references/live-preview.md` when the user asks to see, preview,
  spin, annotate, or send CAD notes from a GLB viewer.
- `cad-coder/references/export-and-downstream.md` when the user asks to print,
  export, drop STEP/STL files, snapshot a variant, or write downstream
  artifacts.
- `cad-coder/references/multipart-and-engineered.md` when the request mentions
  assemblies, multiple parts, load/force/torque, tight fits, non-FDM processes,
  safety, regulated use, high-temperature/engineering filaments, or quantity
  greater than 10.

Do not paste whole reference sections into the chat. Read the needed file, use
the workflow, and report the result.

